@silentbobus: This card [got a remake](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=139668), yet with twice the converted mana cost and unreliable mana gain it's not that playable, though.  

As mentioned before, with removal of mana burn this card is now even better as it already used to be.   
Because of cards like this i don't really get why Wizards decided to remove that game element. Sure, new players didn't get in contact with it too often and might get someday surprised when facing it, but is that a reason to remove it?
